comments.text:
hahaha props to Amy for being very honest and funny because she is 
hilarious! I am a huge fan..

At first I was annoyed because I am very small and petite so I felt like 
Amy was making jokes only at the expense of thin and "pretty" girls. No one 
should be targeted as the expense of a negative joke whether FAT or SKINNY 
or YOUNG or OLD or whatever. 

BUT  I am also very sarcastic like Amy so I understand that her jokes about 
being heavier in LA vs being small are just jokes (with real premise).

I am tiny (5.1) and forever anxious about my height and always wearing 
heels, but I never used to take it seriously when anyone bigger had self 
image issues.  LIKE: who cares if you're bigger at least you are taller 
than me!

Size for any woman is a huge concern in today's society thanks to high body 
image pressure and standards, but hopefully the movement towards healthy 
and fit instead of skinny will overcome these issues.

Amy is so funny and real about female insecurity in today's business and 
social environments and I cannot wait to see what she has to say next!﻿
